http.matchers.docs:
client_asn matches requests by the client_ip GeoIP ASN.

Caddyfile syntax:

	@asn-matcher client_asn "24940"
	respond @asn-matcher "Hetzner Online GmbH"

# Logging

To ERROR level when failed to parse client IP:

	{"level":"error", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_asn","msg":"Failed to parse client IP","client_ip":"...","error":"..."}

To ERROR when failed to get ASN for client IP:

	{"level":"error", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_asn","msg":"Failed to get ASN for client IP","client_ip":"...","error":"..."}

To WARN level when there is no data for the client IP:

	{"level":"warn", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_asn","msg":"No data for client IP","client_ip":"..."}

To INFO level when request matched:

	{"level":"info", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_asn","msg":"Request matched","client_ip":"...", "asn": "..."}

client_country matches requests by the client_ip GeoIP Country.

Caddyfile syntax:

	@country-matcher client_country "HU" "DE"
	respond @country-matcher "Country matcher"

# Logging

To ERROR level when failed to parse client IP:

	{"level":"error", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_country","msg":"Failed to parse client IP","client_ip":"...","error":"..."}

To ERROR when failed to get Country for client IP:

	{"level":"error", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_country","msg":"Failed to get Country for client IP","client_ip":"...","error":"..."}

To WARN level when there is no data for the client IP:

	{"level":"warn", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_country","msg":"No data for client IP","client_ip":"..."}

To INFO level when request matched:

	{"level":"info", ... ,"logger":"http.matchers.client_country","msg":"Request matched","client_ip":"...", "country": "..."}

geoblock implements a request matcher that matches requests based on
geographic location and network information from MaxMind databases.

When a request matches (would be blocked by the geo rules), it returns true,
allowing you to handle matched requests with custom logic such as serving
a static site or redirecting.

The matcher sets various placeholders with geo information that can be used
by downstream handlers:
  - {geoblock.country_code}
  - {geoblock.country_name}
  - {geoblock.city_name}
  - {geoblock.continent_code}
  - {geoblock.subdivision_code}
  - {geoblock.asn}
  - {geoblock.asn_org}
  - {geoblock.latitude}
  - {geoblock.longitude}
  - {geoblock.time_zone}
  - {geoblock.postal_code}
  - {geoblock.blocked}
  - {geoblock.blocked_reason}
